I'm using Elasticsearch version 5.5.0 and I'm experiencing problems regarding dynamic mapping. The configuration "False" isn't working like described here: https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/dynamic.html . I set the mapping for my type to false and I am still able to create new fields that aren't covered by my mapping.
I also experienced the same behavior using reindex.

index settings:
`{"settings": {
    "index": {
      "mapper": {
        "dynamic": false}}}}`

mapping: 
`{"foo": {
    "dynamic": "false",
    "properties": {
      "myField": {
        "type": "text"}}}}`

According to https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/percolator.html

> Also an index can only contain up to one percolator field mapping. Multiple percolator fields will be rejected by the put index and put mapping APIs.

@martijnvg pointed out that this is not an accurate statement, and it's actually easy to verify. The following PUT command works fine:

```
PUT my_test_index
{
  "mappings": {
    "doc": {
      "properties": {
        "query1": {
          "type": "percolator"
        },
        "query2": {
          "type": "percolator"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

I suspect the comment can simply be removed.

